# Architecture

## System Overview

```
                          +------------------+
                          |   Azure DevOps   |
                          |  (tickets, PRs)  |
                          +--------+---------+
                                   |
                  +----------------+----------------+
                  |                                  |
          [Tag added to WI]                  [PR created/commented]
                  |                                  |
                  v                                  v
          +-------+--------+                +--------+-------+
          |  ADO Webhook   |                | ADO Build      |
          |  (service hook)|                | Policy         |
          +-------+--------+                +--------+-------+
                  |                                  |
                  v                                  v
          +-------+--------+                +--------+-------+
          | AWS API Gateway |                | PR Review      |
          +-------+--------+                | Pipeline       |
                  |                          +----------------+
          +-------+--------+
          | Lambda Router  |  (WI Router or PR Router)
          | - dedupe check |
          | - rate limit   |
          | - queue pipeline|
          +-------+--------+
                  |
                  v
          +-------+--------+
          | ADO Pipeline   |  (DoR, DoD, BugFix, DevAgent, etc.)
          | - runs AI agent|
          | - posts results|
          +----------------+

          +-------------------------------------+
          |          Developer's Machine         |
          |                                      |
          |  Claude Code CLI  or  VS Code        |
          |  /dx-req-all         @DxPRReview     |
          |  /dx-plan            @DxCodeReview   |
          |  /dx-step-all        @DxCommit       |
          |                                      |
          |  Reads: .ai/config.yaml              |
          |  Writes: .ai/specs/<id>/             |
          +-------------------------------------+
```

## Two Modes

### Local (Interactive)

The developer runs commands. The AI assists.

```
/dx-req-all <ID>  -->  skill reads config.yaml
                       skill fetches ADO work item
                       skill researches codebase (parallel agents)
                       skill writes .ai/specs/<id>-<slug>/raw-story.md, explain.md, research.md
```

- **Who runs it**: Developer, in their terminal or VS Code
- **Tools**: Claude Code CLI (`/dx-*` commands) or Copilot (`@Agent`)
- **Config**: `.ai/config.yaml` (project settings), `.ai/me.md` (personal tone)
- **Output**: Files in `.ai/specs/`, commits, PRs, ADO comments
- **Control**: Developer approves each action (or runs `/dx-agent-all` for full autonomy)

### Remote (Autonomous)

Events trigger agents. No developer needed.

```
ADO tag added  -->  webhook fires
                    Lambda checks dedupe + rate limit
                    Lambda queues ADO pipeline
                    Pipeline runs AI agent
                    Agent posts ADO comment (or creates PR)
```

- **Who runs it**: Triggered by ADO events (tags, PR creation, PR comments)
- **Infrastructure**: AWS Lambda + DynamoDB + SQS + S3 + API Gateway + CloudWatch
- **Config**: Pipeline variables (API keys, ADO PAT, endpoints)
- **Output**: ADO comments, PR review comments, branches + PRs
- **Control**: Policy gates, rate limits, token budget, scanner

## Plugin System

### Hub and Consumer

```
dx-aem-flow/              <-- Plugin source (Hub)
├── dx/plugins/
│   ├── dx-core/    <-- Core: ADO workflow (43 skills, 5 agents)
│   ├── dx-aem/               <-- AEM: component verification, project knowledge (10 skills, 5 agents)
│   └── dx-automation/        <-- Automation: CI/CD agents (11 skills)
```

- **Hub project** owns the plugin source, AWS infrastructure, and all work-item webhooks
- **Consumer projects** install plugins and get PR pipelines + delegation-ready pipelines
- A project can be both Hub and Consumer (like this one)

### What Plugins Provide

| Layer | Plugin source | Scaffolded to project |
|-------|--------------|----------------------|
| **Skills** | `skills/*/SKILL.md` | Used directly by Claude Code (not copied) |
| **Agents** | `agents/*.md` | Used directly by Claude Code (not copied) |
| **Rules** | `templates/rules/*.template` | `.ai/rules/` and `.claude/rules/` |
| **Docs** | `templates/docs/*.template` | `.ai/docs/` |
| **Config** | `templates/config.yaml.template` | `.ai/config.yaml` |
| **Utilities** | `data/lib/`, `data/hooks/` | `.ai/lib/`, `.claude/hooks/` |
| **Copilot agents** | `templates/agents/*.template` | `.github/agents/` |
| **Automation** | `auto-init` scaffolds | `.ai/automation/` |

### Three-Layer Override

Rules resolve in priority order:

```
1. .ai/rules/<topic>.md           <-- Project override (highest priority)
2. config.yaml overrides: section  <-- Config-level tweak
3. Plugin defaults (rules/*.md)    <-- Plugin default (lowest priority)
```

Projects can also shadow entire skills by creating `.claude/skills/<name>/SKILL.md`.

### Scaffolding Flow

```
/dx-init   -->  scaffold.sh creates .ai/ and .claude/ directories
                copies rules from plugin templates/rules/
                writes .ai/config.yaml from config.yaml.template
                writes .ai/README.md, .ai/docs/*
                optionally installs Copilot agents to .github/agents/

/aem-init  -->  copies AEM convention rules to .claude/rules/
                copies AEM instructions to .github/instructions/

/aem-init  -->  (also) sets up project seed data in .ai/project/
                (project.yaml, file-patterns.yaml, component-index, etc.)

/auto-init -->  scaffolds .ai/automation/ (infra.json, prompts, roles, policy)
                hub: full AWS + webhook setup
                consumer: PR pipelines + delegation only
```

## AWS Infrastructure (Hub Only)

| Resource | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| **API Gateway** (HTTP v2) | Receives ADO webhooks |
| **Lambda: WI Router** | Routes work-item events to the correct pipeline |
| **Lambda: PR Router** | Routes PR comment events to PR Answer pipeline |
| **DynamoDB** | Deduplication (1h TTL), rate limiting, token budget tracking |
| **SQS** | Dead letter queue for failed Lambda invocations |
| **S3** | Pipeline run bundles (inputs, outputs, decision journal) |
| **CloudWatch** | 4 alarms: DLQ depth, WI Router errors, PR Router errors, throttles |
| **SNS** | Alert notifications (email subscription) |

## Key Design Decisions

- **Config-driven**: All project-specific values in `.ai/config.yaml`. Skills never hardcode paths, branches, or URLs.
- **Spec directory convention**: Per-ticket output in `.ai/specs/<id>-<slug>/` with predictable filenames. Skills find each other's output by convention.
- **Fail-closed capabilities**: Agents can only do what their role explicitly allows. Unlisted actions are denied.
- **Headless autonomy**: In pipeline mode, agents never ask questions. They make reasonable decisions and document assumptions.
- **Shared rules**: `.ai/rules/` is read by both local skills and remote pipeline agents. One edit changes behavior everywhere.
